gomodel:SYNGO_5326  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" , "Rationale: Figure 4: proximity labeling of synaptic cleft proteins identified EGFR.\n\nFigure 5: immunofluorescence labeling of overexpressed EGFR showed partial co-localization with VGLUT1 and Bassoon in cortical neuron cultures from rat brain.\n\nFigure 5e: EGFR was also identified in western blots of synaptosome fractions prepared from adult rat brain.. Experimental description: species of the overexpressed protein is not listed, annotating against the identified protein in the proximity labeling assay.\n\n\"We therefore opted to use dissociated neuron culture, rather than intact brain tissue, to allow for rapid delivery and washout of biotin-phenol, H2O2, and subsequent peroxidase quenchers. At DIV19 (19 days in vitro), our embryonic rat cortical neuron cultures displayed abundant staining of synapse markers ...\"\n\nantibody:\nRabbit anti-EGFR, Santa Cruz, Cat# sc-03 RRID: AB_631420" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
